A Ford Kenya splinter group will hold elections countrywide on December 28 to popularise the outfit.Self-appointed interim party leader Ken Wafula said they want to rejuvenate Ford Kenya, which he says has been mismanaged by Senator Moses Wetang ula. We want to hold elections from the grassroots to the national level, Wafula said. He plans to run for the Trans Nzoia Senate seat.Wafula said their Thika National Governing Council meeting last Saturday failed to proceed after Wetang ula s team went to court to stop it.In a statement on Wednesday, Wafula said the party will hold the elections in the sublocations and locations. On December 29, the polls will be held in constituencies and all counties on December 30. On January 28, he said Ford Kenya will hold the National Delegates Congress.